cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of machine learning to enhance Bloom filters, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning, which suggests that it could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Bloom filters in databases, which could place it under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of learned Bloom filters, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
